were taken to the hospital for medical treatment.The Police have opened a case of murder, two counts of
attempted murder and public violence.Meanwhile in the Waterval outside Makhado, it is alleged
that a group of community members in Njakanjaka village mobilised themselves
complaining about the alleged gangsters who are terrorising them by stealing
their properties and breaking into their spaza shops.Ngoepe said following this mobilisation, the community
started tracking down alleged gang members.They apprehended one of them who is his 20's and started
assaulting him with various objects and subsequently killing him instantly. He said the deceased is still unknown at this stage.  Police in Waterval have opened cases of murder and public
violence.Provincial Commissioners General Nneke Ledwaba said
members of the community must stop taking the law in their own hands and if
they have information about any suspected persons involved in crime. He said they must call the Police rather than to engage
in this heinous acts which is totally uncalled for.Anyone with information which can lead to the arrest of
all the suspects involved in these incidents may contact the crime stop number
0860010111 or the crime line sms 32211 or the nearest Police Station.